---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const candidates = [
  { id: 'typescript', name: 'TypeScript', status: 'Current reference', description: 'The working compiler and complete 41 × 4 evidence catalog.', href: '/typescript/', detail: '164 browser-verified surfaces' },
  { id: 'go', name: 'Go', status: 'Coming soon', description: 'Native binary candidate focused on simple distribution, startup time, and concurrency.', detail: 'Benchmark implementation pending' },
  { id: 'rust', name: 'Rust', status: 'Coming soon', description: 'Native candidate focused on throughput, memory use, correctness, and parallel compilation.', detail: 'Benchmark implementation pending' },
  { id: 'zig', name: 'Zig', status: 'Coming soon', description: 'Small native binary candidate with explicit allocation and a minimal runtime surface.', detail: 'Benchmark implementation pending' },
];
---
<Layout title="Kumo compiler candidates">
  <header class="intro">
    <p class="eyebrow">Kumo compiler study</p>
    <h1>Which implementation should compile Kumo?</h1>
    <p>We have one working TypeScript reference compiler. Next we will implement the same normalized contract in Go, Rust, and Zig, run each against the same 41-component fixture set, and compare output correctness, build throughput, startup time, memory, binary size, and maintenance cost before choosing a reference implementation.</p>
  </header>

  <section class="rules" aria-labelledby="rules-title"><h2 id="rules-title">One benchmark contract</h2><p>Every candidate must consume the same <code>kumo.ir/v1</code> input, produce equivalent framework source, pass the same browser and provenance gates, and report raw repeatable measurements. A faster compiler does not win if its output or developer workflow is weaker.</p></section>

  <section class="candidates" aria-labelledby="candidate-title"><div class="heading"><h2 id="candidate-title">Compiler candidates</h2><p>TypeScript is available now. The native implementations are intentionally marked pending until real code and measurements exist.</p></div><div class="grid">
    {candidates.map(candidate => candidate.href ? <a class="card active" href={candidate.href}><span class="status">{candidate.status}</span><h3>{candidate.name}</h3><p>{candidate.description}</p><small>{candidate.detail}</small><b>View compiler results →</b></a> : <article class="card"><span class="status pending">{candidate.status}</span><h3>{candidate.name}</h3><p>{candidate.description}</p><small>{candidate.detail}</small></article>)}
  </div></section>

  <section class="roadmap" aria-labelledby="roadmap-title"><div class="heading"><h2 id="roadmap-title">Roadmap</h2><p>The TypeScript implementation is working. The comparison and product layers are next.</p></div><ol>
    <li class="done"><span>1</span><div><strong>TypeScript reference compiler</strong><p>Done for the current 41 executable targets: normalized IR, native framework outputs, package provenance, and selected browser evidence. It is a working reference—not yet proof that TypeScript is the best implementation.</p></div><b>Done</b></li>
    <li><span>2</span><div><strong>Go, Rust, and Zig implementations</strong><p>Implement the same contract, validate equivalent outputs, and collect raw benchmark samples for throughput, startup, memory, and distribution size.</p></div><b>Next</b></li>
    <li><span>3</span><div><strong>Choose the compiler</strong><p>Compare correctness, performance, maintainability, ecosystem fit, and operational complexity. Pick one from evidence rather than preference.</p></div><b>Planned</b></li>
    <li><span>4</span><div><strong>Developer and agent experience</strong><p>Design how people and agents install, import, generate, inspect, and update Kumo for Svelte, Vue, and Solid. Test upstream-change regeneration and prepare the technical proposal for Brandon and Brayden.</p></div><b>Planned</b></li>
  </ol></section>
</Layout>
<style>
.intro{max-width:850px;padding:34px 0 14px}.eyebrow{margin:0 0 12px;color:#64748b;font-size:12px;font-weight:750;letter-spacing:.08em;text-transform:uppercase}.intro h1{margin:0;font-size:clamp(38px,5vw,58px);line-height:1.05;letter-spacing:-.045em}.intro>p:last-child{margin:22px 0 0;color:#475569;font-size:18px;line-height:1.65}.rules{max-width:850px;margin-top:42px;padding-top:22px;border-top:1px solid #d8dde5}.rules h2,.roadmap h2,.heading h2{margin:0;font-size:24px;letter-spacing:-.025em}.rules p,.heading p{margin:8px 0 0;color:#64748b;line-height:1.6}.candidates{margin-top:48px}.heading{display:flex;align-items:end;justify-content:space-between;gap:30px;margin-bottom:16px}.heading p{max-width:540px;font-size:13px}.grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,minmax(0,1fr));gap:12px}.card{display:block;min-height:210px;padding:20px;border:1px solid #d8dde5;border-radius:10px;background:#fff;color:inherit;text-decoration:none}.card.active{border-color:#94a3b8}.card.active:hover{border-color:#475569}.status{display:inline-block;color:#166534;font-size:11px;font-weight:750;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.05em}.status.pending{color:#64748b}.card h3{margin:14px 0 8px;font-size:25px;letter-spacing:-.03em}.card p{margin:0;color:#475569;line-height:1.55}.card small{display:block;margin-top:22px;color:#64748b}.card b{display:block;margin-top:14px;color:#0759b6;font-size:13px}.roadmap{margin-top:48px}.roadmap ol{display:grid;gap:0;margin:16px 0 0;padding:0;border:1px solid #d8dde5;border-radius:10px;background:#fff;list-style:none}.roadmap li{display:grid;grid-template-columns:30px 1fr auto;gap:14px;align-items:start;padding:18px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb}.roadmap li:first-child{border-top:0}.roadmap li>span{display:grid;width:27px;height:27px;place-items:center;border:1px solid #cbd5e1;border-radius:50%;color:#64748b;font-size:12px;font-weight:750}.roadmap li.done>span{border-color:#16a34a;background:#dcfce7;color:#166534}.roadmap li strong{font-size:15px}.roadmap li p{margin:5px 0 0;color:#64748b;font-size:13px;line-height:1.55}.roadmap li>b{color:#64748b;font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.05em}.roadmap li.done>b{color:#166534}@media(max-width:700px){.heading{display:block}.grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}.intro>p:last-child{font-size:16px}.card{min-height:0}}
</style>
